## Objective
Add file upload to the Agent Editor's context pack section (step-level context).

## Working Directory
`Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/builder/editors/`

## Context
The `AgentEditor` component has a Context Packs section where users add context chips (kind: document, data_view, schema, sop, retrieval, memory). Currently it's a text-based form with label, kind dropdown, and source ref input.

Add a file upload option that:
1. Shows an "Upload File" button alongside the "+ Add Context" button
2. When clicked, opens a file input (hidden native `<input type='file'>`)
3. On file selection, reads the file as base64, POSTs to `/api/files` with `scope: 'step'`, `workflow_id` and `step_id` from props
4. On success, creates a context pack with `kind: 'document'`, `label: filename`, `sourceRef: 'file://file_id'`
5. Shows upload progress/status

Read `AgentEditor.tsx` first. Find the context packs section. Modify it to add the file upload option.

The upload button should appear next to the existing "+ Add Context" button:
```tsx
<div style={{display:'flex', gap: 6}}>
  <button className="editor-add-btn" onClick={() => setShowAddContext(true)} style={{flex:1}}>+ Add Context</button>
  <button className="editor-add-btn" onClick={() => fileInputRef.current?.click()} style={{flex:1}}>Upload File</button>
  <input ref={fileInputRef} type="file" hidden onChange={handleFileUpload} />
</div>
```

`handleFileUpload` function:
```typescript
const handleFileUpload = async (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
  const file = e.target.files?.[0];
  if (!file) return;

  const reader = new FileReader();
  reader.onload = async () => {
    const base64 = (reader.result as string).split(',')[1]; // strip data:...;base64, prefix
    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/files', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          filename: file.name,
          content: base64,
          content_type: file.type || 'application/octet-stream',
          scope: 'step',
          workflow_id: '', // will be set on save
          step_id: step.id,
          description: `Uploaded for step: ${step.label || step.id}`,
        }),
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      if (res.ok && data.id) {
        // Add as context pack
        const packs = [...(step.contextPacks || [])];
        packs.push({
          id: 'cp_' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8),
          label: file.name,
          kind: 'document',
          sourceRef: `file://${data.id}`,
        });
        onUpdate({ contextPacks: packs });
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('File upload failed:', err);
    }
  };
  reader.readAsDataURL(file);
  // Reset input so same file can be uploaded again
  e.target.value = '';
};
```

Also update context chip rendering — if a context pack has `sourceRef` starting with `file://`, show a small file icon or "📄" before the label.

